Key Match Events: Fred VanVleet scored 15 points and stole the Lakers' inbounds pass intended for James with 5.7 seconds remaining and the Rockets up by three
Anthony Davis scored 22 of his 30 points in the second half and grabbed 13 rebounds
James scored 21 points with 13 rebounds and nine assists
Post-Match Reflections: The Rockets held off LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers, 119-115
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets opened the final period on a 10-0 run and every time the Lakers got close managed to pull away again
Others: The New Orleans Pelicans, fueled by 25 points from CJ McCollum and a triple-double of 14 points, 10 rebounds and 12 assists from Dejounte Murray, beat the Wizards, 110-98, in Washington
